            . I know Mr. Cook's house at <placeName id="t18250519-13-crimeloc80">Tottenham</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18250519-13-crimeloc80" type="placeName" value="Tottenham"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18250519-13-crimeloc80" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250519-13-off78 t18250519-13-crimeloc80"></join>. About four o'clock on the 11th of May I saw the prisoner come out of the ground floor window of Mr. Cook's house, with a bundle in his hand; I ran and told my father, who went and took him from a wash-house, which he ran into, when he heard me give the alarm.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250519-13-person170">
                  WILLIAM 
                  LAWRENCE
               <interp inst="t18250519-13-person170" type="surname" value="LAWRENCE"></interp>
